I don't think you can - you can only test if they are random *in
relation to the factors you measured*.

These frogs could have a preference for the ponds with a certain
characteristic X, but which is not reflected in any of your measured
factors - so *in regards of the factors measured*, the distribution is
random, but still highly dependent on the factor X.

Bottomline: I think you have to refine your question before you can answer it.

Cheers,

Rainer

